#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
pull-backup: Pull backups over SSH (WireGuard), snapshot+retention.

Preserved core behaviors:
- Scheduler-driven: requires --daemon.
- Preflight reachability = ssh works AND remote has rsync.
- Resumable snapshots via snapshots/.inprogress-<device>/.run-tag
- Dual logging:
  - stdout (journald via systemd)
  - per-job logfile under .../<class>/<device>/logs/
- Retention: keep N snapshots per job (default 3).
- Progress: periodic bytes-so-far + rate using du on the inprogress dir (no rsync --progress).
- Stall watchdog: kill rsync only if "no progress" for --stall-timeout-s.

Behavior improvements kept / expanded:
- "quarantine" directory concept renamed to legacy/ (back-compat: action=quarantine accepted but writes into legacy/).
- Off-days: resumables can run even if schedule doesn't match (controlled).
- Better preflight ordering: resumables first, prior failures, then oldest successful backup (ledger), then oldest snapshot, etc.
- Optional idle archiving: compress legacy snapshots into archives/<class>/<device>/<tag>.tar.zst using zstd -12.

New in this version (per your requirements):
A) Correctness:
- Never finalize snapshots unless rsync reached terminal success (rc=0) or an explicitly finalized soft-success (23/24).
- Retry exhaustion on transient rc -> FAILED attempts_exhausted(last_rc=...); leave .inprogress intact.

B) Permission denied handling:
- Classify "Permission denied (13)" read errors from rsync output and collect offending paths.
- If rc=23/24 and ONLY permission-denied read errors occurred:
  - re-run rsync once in the SAME run with runtime --exclude for each denied path (same tag/inprogress).
  - aim to reach rc==0 while explicitly skipping unreadable files.
- Persist auto-excludes in state dir: <device>.autoexclude (opt-in via --auto-ignore-perms; default ON).
- Cap exclude growth via --auto-ignore-max.

C) Stall reliability:
- Stall requires BOTH no byte growth AND no rsync output activity for stall timeout.

D) Configurable excludes:
- jobs.toml supports:
  - exclude = ["pattern", ...]           # rsync --exclude
  - exclude_file = "/path/to/file"       # rsync --exclude-from
  - stall_timeout_s / progress_interval_s / du_timeout_s (per-job overrides)

E) Durable ledger:
- JSONL ledger in state dir: runs.jsonl (one record per job completion; archive events too).

F) Notifications (opt-in):
- --notify uses notify-send if available + graphical session; logs NOTIFY_SKIP otherwise.

I) Self-backup safety:
- If job appears local (ssh=localhost/127.0.0.1/<hostname>), force-exclude backups root under the job path.
"""

